BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..subtitle: Warlock Vanguard
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Ikora Rey
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: The wise Ikora Rey aids and advises Guardians in the protection of humanity and beyond.

displayProperties.description: Vex Data Seeds are archetypal constructs that hold fundamental source code, allowing the creation of a variety of weapons.
displayProperties.name: Vex Data Seeds

displayProperties.description: Reconnaissance and requisition tasks for the Vanguard's counteroffensive against the Vex incursion on the Moon.
displayProperties.name: Vex Offensive Bounties

interactions.flavorLineOne: There's a chill in the air, but Ikora's warm greeting is that of a friend. She rewards you for your performance, and wishes you a happy Dawning.
As the Dawning comes to a close, Ikora has one last reward to give to her favorite Guardian —and friend.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak to Ikora about what you did to help Eris with the phantoms that haunted her.
headerDisplayProperties.name: As a Friend

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Ikora believes Eris is more than just an ally. She's a friend. One you've stood by through thick and thin. 

Ikora thanks you. She feels nothing but admiration and appreciation for you and your efforts in helping Eris Morn on the Moon.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak to Ikora at the Tower about the data you collected in the Black Garden.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Patternbreaking

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Ikora has analyzed the data you collected, and it all points to a single conclusion: the Vex have resurrected the Undying Mind, a Hydra built to seize control of the Black Garden. It appears to be hiding itself in multiple co-occurrent timelines. Ikora intends to devise a plan to deal with this new threat but needs time to sort out the details.

Continue your efforts in the Vex Offensive activity while Ikora develops her plan.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak to Ikora in the Tower about the latest developments in her plan to destroy the newly resurrected Undying Mind.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Pardon Our Dust

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Ikora wishes you a happy Festival of the Lost and apprises you of her progress on the Vex portal, where construction is proceeding as planned. But there's more work to be done before the portal can be put to use.

Enjoy the Festival of the Lost while Ikora continues work on the Vex portal.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak with Ikora about the latest developments in her plan to slay the Undying Mind.
headerDisplayProperties.name: To Destroy a Mind

interactions.flavorLineOne:
The portal is completed. Now, at last, the final phase of Ikora's plan to eliminate the Undying Mind can be put into practice. She and Zavala have tested the hardware extensively, locating and destroying dozens of instantiations of the Undying Mind—but there are hundreds, if not thousands, of copies still lurking in the Garden. This task now falls to you.

Enter the Black Garden to locate and defeat the Undying Mind.

"The Festival of the Lost honors those who have passed on," Ikora says. "Sad, yes, but also happy—we are still here to preserve their memories."

She smiles. "That's something to celebrate. So go on, lead the celebration. Eva has some very clever masks this year."

"The Festival of the Lost honors those who have passed on," Ikora says. "Sad, yes, but also happy—we are still here to preserve their memories."

She smiles. "That's something to celebrate. So go on, lead the celebration. And please, accept a few extra sweets from me. Zavala and I are still very grateful for your loyalty."

headerDisplayProperties.description: Ikora Rey has heard of your success in saving Saint-14 from the Infinite Forest and wishes to thank you. Visit her in the Tower Annex.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Ikora Rey

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Ikora gives you her heartfelt thanks for rescuing Saint-14. It's not often that a tragic loss can be undone. She cautions you against making a habit of experimenting with other timelines, though.

She tells you her Hidden will monitor the Sundial, and asks for your help in continuing to thwart the Red Legion's efforts on Mercury.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Ikora Rey has heard of your victory over the Undying Mind and wishes to congratulate you. Visit her in the Tower Annex.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Ikora Rey

interactions.flavorLineOne: Ikora congratulates you on your victory over the Undying Mind. As always, she is impressed by your dedication to protecting the City from the enemies of humanity, and she thanks you for your bravery.

headerDisplayProperties.description: With renewed purpose, Ikora has resumed her role as head of Vanguard Research. Find her in the Bazaar and see how she's doing.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Ikora Rey

interactions.flavorLineOne:
You changed the future—and in doing so, helped Ikora, Osiris, and Sagira change their present.

With a true friend by your side, the possibilities are infinite.
Ikora gives a small smile at the familiar-looking confection. Perhaps her connection to the Traveler runs deeper than you thought.

Your discoveries within the Pyramid are key to the future and survival of all—but the Nightmares continue their attack across the entire system, beyond our Moon. They must not be allowed to spread any further.

Stay vigilant. Keep Nightmares at bay on every planet.

Our fight has only just begun.
As you gave her the book you could swear you saw a hint of a smile on Ikora's face, but it's already gone.

"Welcome, Guardian. There are many worlds to explore, and countless treasures to discover."

Ikora Rey offers special rewards to Guardians who explore destinations, alone or with friends.

Hover over the quest icon below, and select it with .


ACQUIRE QUEST

"Your bravery inspires, Guardian."

As you continue to explore destinations, more world quests will become available to you.

Check in with faction vendors across the solar system regularly to acquire new quests and rewards.

To find Panoptes, you'll need a map of the Infinite Forest. Ikora believes you can find one in the Pyramidion on Io.

Retrieve the map by completing mission "Deep Storage" on Io.

Ikora realized that the more we learn, the less we know. She now reflects on past events and meditates on the bright future promised by a reborn and living Traveler. She has also found in you a friend, someone she can trust. For her, that can be rare. 

Return to Ikora Rey to relive past Red War activities.

Zavala has forbidden Guardians from traveling to the Reef for fear of starting a war with Uldren. So, officially, Ikora can't help you.

But unofficially, Ikora tips you off that Uldren and his Fallen Barons have gathered on a stretch of the Reef known as the Tangled Shore. If you want revenge, there's the place to start.

Take a hint from Ikora and investigate the Tangled Shore in mission "High Plains Blues."

You've rid the system of Cayde's killers, and Ikora sleeps easier at night because of it. But she still worries about the future of the Vanguard. The Hunters are without a leader. Zavala is more withdrawn than ever. And Ikora wonders if the worst is yet to come.
Complete mission "Omega" on Mercury.

Ikora nods when you tell her about the malfunctioning frame. "Interesting timing," she says. "I just received a report from the Hidden that the Leviathan has deployed some kind of barge to the surface of Nessus."

She sizes you up. "If you want to investigate this on your own, I have no issue with that—but you're not going alone. Let me patch you the coordinates of the barge. I'll send other Guardians after you."

"The more you explore, the closer we come to reclaiming our lost worlds and the countless treasures they hide."

Each destination holds its own mysteries, adventures, and rewards. Visit the faction vendors on each destination. Complete the world quests they offer to gain XP and rewards, including powerful new weapons.
With a knowing look, Ikora hands you a package. "Aunor asked me to give this to you," she says, smiling.
Your reputation in the Crucible precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
